1
00:01:38,920 --> 00:01:41,206
[Episode 13]

2
00:01:42,439 --> 00:01:43,832
Flies!

3
00:01:44,519 --> 00:01:45,560
Wu.

4
00:01:45,560 --> 00:01:47,200
Why all the zapping so early?

5
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:49,359
Are there really that many flies?

6
00:01:49,359 --> 00:01:51,760
Grandma. There are too many flies today.

7
00:01:51,760 --> 00:01:54,245
They all flew in this morning.

8
00:01:54,879 --> 00:01:56,232
Good morning, Grandma.

9
00:01:56,232 --> 00:01:57,279
Grandma.

10
00:01:57,279 --> 00:01:59,760
You're Qing Ye's classmate, right?

11
00:01:59,760 --> 00:02:01,480
Are you here to study English?

12
00:02:01,480 --> 00:02:04,200
You're such a diligent learner!

13
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:06,170
Diligent learner?

14
00:02:10,359 --> 00:02:13,239
He's hiding his real
intentions behind studying.

15
00:02:13,239 --> 00:02:15,239
Don't talk nonsense.

16
00:02:15,239 --> 00:02:16,320
Have some food.

17
00:02:16,320 --> 00:02:17,532
You can read while you eat.

18
00:02:17,532 --> 00:02:20,657
It's okay.
I don't usually eat much in the morning.

19
00:02:20,657 --> 00:02:23,880
You can share some
with the landlord and Grandma.

20
00:02:23,880 --> 00:02:26,679
I'll come by every morning
to practice English with you

21
00:02:26,679 --> 00:02:28,720
and bring you breakfast.

22
00:02:28,720 --> 00:02:30,200
Do you have a microwave?

23
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:31,440
No.

24
00:02:31,440 --> 00:02:33,760
This is a hair salon, not a diner.

25
00:02:33,760 --> 00:02:35,870
We don't have time to host you.

26
00:02:38,720 --> 00:02:40,732
Nonsense!

27
00:02:40,732 --> 00:02:41,760
Good morning, Mrs. Xing.

28
00:02:41,760 --> 00:02:43,270
Morning.

29
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:46,132
You can't leave yet.

30
00:02:47,079 --> 00:02:48,770
Auntie.

31
00:02:48,770 --> 00:02:51,320
You bought so much breakfast.

32
00:02:51,320 --> 00:02:53,639
Have more.

33
00:02:53,639 --> 00:02:55,782
Come here, young man. Come with me.

34
00:02:55,782 --> 00:02:56,839
Where?

35
00:02:56,839 --> 00:02:57,880
You'll find out soon.

36
00:02:57,880 --> 00:02:59,907
Come over here.

37
00:03:02,040 --> 00:03:03,920
Come here, young man.

38
00:03:03,920 --> 00:03:05,320
Mrs Xing, what are you doing?

39
00:03:05,320 --> 00:03:07,320
Get a haircut before you go.

40
00:03:07,320 --> 00:03:08,720
My... My hair...

41
00:03:08,720 --> 00:03:11,239
All visitors are guests. Right?

42
00:03:11,239 --> 00:03:12,720
You can't leave without

43
00:03:12,720 --> 00:03:14,000
getting a haircut.

44
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:16,480
I don't plan to get a haircut lately.

45
00:03:16,480 --> 00:03:18,770
It's fine. Just throw it in.

46
00:03:18,770 --> 00:03:22,332
Since you're Ye's classmate,

47
00:03:22,332 --> 00:03:25,382
I'll give you a discount. Pick one.

48
00:03:46,320 --> 00:03:49,280
Why did you stop swatting flies?

49
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:51,799
I'll let them live.

50
00:03:52,799 --> 00:03:54,645
You're quite popular.

51
00:03:54,645 --> 00:03:56,600
Some boy showed up early

52
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:59,070
to learn English with you.

53
00:04:00,880 --> 00:04:04,440
He's here for English practice,

54
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:07,399
and gets a haircut on the side.

55
00:04:07,399 --> 00:04:09,040
What a win!

56
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:11,040
So, what do you think of this customer?

57
00:04:11,040 --> 00:04:13,079
He seems easygoing.

58
00:04:13,079 --> 00:04:15,520
He might be an impulsive spender.

59
00:04:16,239 --> 00:04:19,080
Who knows if he'll spend on impulse or not.

60
00:04:19,080 --> 00:04:21,520
You've sparked her drive to make money.

61
00:04:21,520 --> 00:04:23,119
Now that she's enjoyed the profits.

62
00:04:23,119 --> 00:04:25,559
She'd sign up even a fly that flies past

63
00:04:25,559 --> 00:04:27,080
Xuan Island for a haircut.

64
00:04:27,080 --> 00:04:28,554
But you've killed all the flies.

65
00:04:28,554 --> 00:04:30,679
How can she style them?

66
00:04:30,679 --> 00:04:32,774
I can't kill them all.

67
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:36,480
Men's custom styling.

68
00:04:36,480 --> 00:04:38,640
But I'm a student.

69
00:04:38,640 --> 00:04:40,559
Students can rock a great style as well!

70
00:04:40,559 --> 00:04:41,799
Right?

71
00:04:41,799 --> 00:04:43,532
Mrs. Xing, why don't you pick one for me?

72
00:04:43,532 --> 00:04:44,545
I'll...

73
00:04:44,545 --> 00:04:46,882
Let's go with this one then.

74
00:04:46,882 --> 00:04:48,760
Okay.

75
00:04:48,760 --> 00:04:50,520
Great.

76
00:04:53,595 --> 00:04:54,595
Qing Ye.

77
00:04:54,595 --> 00:04:56,305
I got a new haircut.

78
00:04:58,480 --> 00:04:59,720
This...

79
00:04:59,720 --> 00:05:01,439
This... This...

80
00:05:01,439 --> 00:05:03,799
I even got a membership card.

81
00:05:03,799 --> 00:05:05,319
How much did you top up?

82
00:05:05,319 --> 00:05:07,757
888 yuan.

83
00:05:08,439 --> 00:05:10,119
888 yuan?

84
00:05:10,119 --> 00:05:12,280
Isn't that a bit much?

85
00:05:12,280 --> 00:05:15,157
Not much. It's a good deal to top up.

86
00:05:15,840 --> 00:05:19,319
Ye, Ye Ying Jian is so generous.

87
00:05:19,319 --> 00:05:20,600
Let me tell you.

88
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:25,022
Ye put a lot of thought into this price list.

89
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:27,989
Come back anytime!

90
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:31,239
Mom,

91
00:05:31,239 --> 00:05:33,570
you're obsessed with money.

92
00:05:33,570 --> 00:05:34,720
No.

93
00:05:34,720 --> 00:05:36,879
Topping up is really a good deal.

94
00:05:36,879 --> 00:05:38,040
I did the math.

95
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:40,439
It's basically 50% off.

96
00:05:40,439 --> 00:05:43,207
I can come to see you over 40 times a semester.

97
00:05:43,207 --> 00:05:45,439
It includes a wash, cut, blow-dry,

98
00:05:45,439 --> 00:05:47,257
and even styling.

99
00:05:47,257 --> 00:05:51,080
Xuan Island has been around for ten years.

100
00:05:51,080 --> 00:05:53,239
I'd never make dirty money.

101
00:05:53,239 --> 00:05:56,920
Besides, he comes here to learn English from Ye

102
00:05:56,920 --> 00:05:58,840
and gets a haircut on the side.

103
00:05:58,840 --> 00:06:01,199
It's killing two birds with one stone.

104
00:06:01,199 --> 00:06:05,359
Mom, he's a student.
A student's job is to study.

105
00:06:05,359 --> 00:06:07,770
Students ought to concentrate on learning,

106
00:06:07,770 --> 00:06:08,857
not styling their hair.

107
00:06:08,857 --> 00:06:11,549
40 times? He'll go bald.

108
00:06:13,679 --> 00:06:15,119
I agree with that.

109
00:06:15,119 --> 00:06:18,119
Students should focus on their studies.

110
00:06:18,119 --> 00:06:21,080
- Exactly.
- Not to become Master Xing in Xinhai County,

111
00:06:21,080 --> 00:06:24,307
still less Boss Xing in Shunyi.

112
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:29,070
Right, Grandma?

113
00:06:29,070 --> 00:06:32,240
Ye is absolutely right.

114
00:06:34,183 --> 00:06:35,195
Qing Ye,

115
00:06:35,195 --> 00:06:37,672
what do you think of this cut?

116
00:06:39,895 --> 00:06:40,920
I think

117
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:43,657
it suits you perfectly.

118
00:06:43,657 --> 00:06:46,240
Today, let's congratulate Ye Ying Jian

119
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:48,879
on becoming our VVIP.

120
00:06:48,879 --> 00:06:54,309
We must give him our best service. Right?

121
00:06:54,960 --> 00:06:56,160
Ying Jian,

122
00:06:56,160 --> 00:06:57,887
I'll shape your eyebrows for free. Let's go.

123
00:06:57,887 --> 00:06:59,559
Shape my eyebrows?

124
00:06:59,559 --> 00:07:03,080
How?

125
00:07:03,080 --> 00:07:04,199
You'll know.

126
00:07:04,199 --> 00:07:06,145
Come on.

127
00:07:20,345 --> 00:07:22,307
Shu Han.

128
00:07:23,307 --> 00:07:24,907
Ying Jian.

129
00:07:24,907 --> 00:07:26,199
You've got a new look.

130
00:07:26,199 --> 00:07:28,848
This new hairstyle suits me, doesn't it?

131
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:30,960
It really suits you.

132
00:07:30,960 --> 00:07:31,999
Look.

133
00:07:31,999 --> 00:07:33,020
I also got my eyebrows trimmed.

134
00:07:33,020 --> 00:07:35,257
Very handsome.

135
00:07:35,257 --> 00:07:36,782
- Shu Han.
- Qing Ye.

136
00:07:36,782 --> 00:07:38,720
We make a nice pair

137
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:42,559
for the school event,
Qing Ye and I, with this hairstyle, huh?

138
00:07:42,559 --> 00:07:44,439
No, no, no. I'm not good enough.

139
00:07:44,439 --> 00:07:45,840
I have to catch the bus.

140
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:47,679
Shu Han, I... I'll head out first.

141
00:07:47,679 --> 00:07:48,960
Wait, Qing Ye.

142
00:07:48,960 --> 00:07:50,080
I'll go with you.

143
00:07:50,080 --> 00:07:51,559
Together?

144
00:07:51,559 --> 00:07:54,720
Shu Han, sorry you made a wasted trip.

145
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:57,040
I haven't taken the bus in a long time.

146
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:58,480
I want to experience it again.

147
00:07:58,480 --> 00:07:59,759
Sure. No problem.

148
00:07:59,759 --> 00:08:02,199
I have something to discuss with Xing Wu.
You guys go ahead.

149
00:08:02,199 --> 00:08:03,400
You're here.

150
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:06,170
You drive.
I'll handle some business on the way.

151
00:08:06,170 --> 00:08:07,600
Off you go. Bye-bye!

152
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:09,400
Bye-bye.

153
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:31,720
Bye.

154
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:33,559
Bro. Well.

155
00:08:33,559 --> 00:08:36,559
- You look very happy.
- Yes!

156
00:08:36,559 --> 00:08:40,707
Get me two extra dishes for lunch today.

157
00:08:40,707 --> 00:08:43,157
Did you win the lottery or something?

158
00:08:43,157 --> 00:08:44,280
Well.

159
00:08:44,280 --> 00:08:47,040
It's pretty much like winning the lottery.

160
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:48,932
Look.

161
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:53,000
Lucky 888, may you get rich!

162
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,815
Someone's topping up their membership card?

163
00:08:54,815 --> 00:08:56,719
What a great
start to the day!

164
00:08:56,719 --> 00:08:59,000
Fortune has arrived!
Of course I'm off to a great start!

165
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:01,040
I need to soak up some of your luck.

166
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:04,532
I want to be successful too.

167
00:09:08,160 --> 00:09:12,400
Before we start,
I'd like to gauge everyone's level.

168
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:14,582
Please read this passage.

169
00:09:14,582 --> 00:09:16,599
- Let's start with you.
- Okay.

170
00:09:16,599 --> 00:09:18,720
Welcome to our remarkable

171
00:09:18,720 --> 00:09:21,719
No.1 Middle School of Anzi County.

172
00:09:21,719 --> 00:09:25,880
It's surrounded by beautiful seaside scenery.

173
00:09:25,880 --> 00:09:28,240
Great. Next.

174
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:30,182
Come on.

175
00:09:32,079 --> 00:09:33,820
Here I go.

176
00:09:34,439 --> 00:09:40,332
Welcome... to our... remarkable...

177
00:09:40,332 --> 00:09:42,679
No. 1... Middle...

178
00:09:42,679 --> 00:09:44,199
No. 1.

179
00:09:44,199 --> 00:09:47,719
Welcome to our...

180
00:09:47,719 --> 00:09:49,520
Welcome to our...

181
00:09:49,520 --> 00:09:55,507
remarkable No.1 Middle School of Anzi County...

182
00:09:55,507 --> 00:09:56,920
Surrounded...

183
00:09:56,920 --> 00:09:58,760
Remark...

184
00:09:58,760 --> 00:10:00,000
Remark...

185
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:01,400
Remarkable.

186
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:03,199
I-I-Is this written wrong?

187
00:10:03,199 --> 00:10:05,880
I-I-I can't read it smoothly.

188
00:10:05,880 --> 00:10:09,432
I recognize each letter,
just not the whole thing.

189
00:10:09,432 --> 00:10:13,920
- Sit down.
- Beautiful seaside scenery.

190
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:15,920
Pretty good.

191
00:10:15,920 --> 00:10:20,400
Okay, I've roughly gauged where you all stand.

192
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:23,040
It seems your vocabulary is a bit limited.

193
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:25,760
But vocabulary is the most important
part of learning English.

194
00:10:25,760 --> 00:10:28,760
If your vocabulary improves,
your grades will follow.

195
00:10:28,760 --> 00:10:32,357
- So, we'll start by memorizing vocabulary.
- Okay.

196
00:10:32,357 --> 00:10:34,599
Wait, wait, wait. No, Cousin.

197
00:10:34,599 --> 00:10:36,959
We're not good at studying.

198
00:10:36,959 --> 00:10:39,439
Memorizing words is such a struggle for us.

199
00:10:39,439 --> 00:10:40,570
Yeah.

200
00:10:40,570 --> 00:10:44,880
W-W-We grew up without exposure to English.

201
00:10:44,880 --> 00:10:49,345
W-W-We went to work early to make a living.

202
00:10:53,132 --> 00:10:54,182
Come on.

203
00:10:54,182 --> 00:10:55,240
I promised

204
00:10:55,240 --> 00:10:58,479
the teacher I'd get the English Corner
up and running.

205
00:10:58,479 --> 00:11:00,160
I'll stick with it to help you

206
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:02,495
improve your English.

207
00:11:02,495 --> 00:11:04,199
Don't give up. Learn English well.

208
00:11:04,199 --> 00:11:06,199
Let's do this together!
We'll keep going, alright?

209
00:11:06,199 --> 00:11:07,515
Okay!

210
00:11:08,199 --> 00:11:09,640
By the way, Hu,

211
00:11:09,640 --> 00:11:11,845
can you do rap?

212
00:11:21,079 --> 00:11:22,400
Rapping Chu Shi Biao

213
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:23,799
could make

214
00:11:23,799 --> 00:11:26,247
it a lot easier.

215
00:11:46,120 --> 00:11:47,959
[Custom Badges]

216
00:11:47,959 --> 00:11:49,000
Hello.

217
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:50,000
Well.

218
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:51,160
Can you help me

219
00:11:51,160 --> 00:11:53,400
print these onto these badges?

220
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:54,760
It's in English, right?

221
00:11:54,760 --> 00:11:56,080
Yes, yes, it's in English.

222
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:58,280
No problem.

223
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:10,272
[English Corner Plan]

224
00:12:15,160 --> 00:12:18,960
Welcome to our English Corner.

225
00:12:19,959 --> 00:12:22,520
Everyone who joins

226
00:12:22,520 --> 00:12:24,839
the English Corner will receive

227
00:12:24,839 --> 00:12:26,240
a custom badge.

228
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:27,240
Look.

229
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:29,079
They feature

230
00:12:29,079 --> 00:12:30,520
grammar,

231
00:12:30,520 --> 00:12:32,079
sentence structures,

232
00:12:32,079 --> 00:12:34,000
words and phrases

233
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:36,799
to help you memorize them daily.

234
00:12:36,799 --> 00:12:40,760
I hope these badges show everyone
that English isn't hard.

235
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:41,880
With the right methods,

236
00:12:41,880 --> 00:12:46,240
memorizing words and learning grammar
can be really fun.

237
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:47,599
Take Hu for example.

238
00:12:47,599 --> 00:12:49,439
Fan Tong is

239
00:12:49,439 --> 00:12:52,199
going to rap for us and share

240
00:12:52,199 --> 00:12:55,920
how to learn vocabulary without stress.

241
00:12:55,920 --> 00:12:57,599
Everyone, give him a beat.

242
00:12:57,599 --> 00:13:00,160
Five, six, seven, go!

243
00:13:00,160 --> 00:13:02,839
♪ Welcome to
a totally different English class ♪

244
00:13:02,839 --> 00:13:05,920
♪ Today we learn words with rap ♪

245
00:13:05,920 --> 00:13:07,559
♪ Don't stress out ♪

246
00:13:07,559 --> 00:13:10,640
♪ Only a handful of words ♪

247
00:13:10,640 --> 00:13:12,439
♪ and a verb suffix ♪

248
00:13:12,439 --> 00:13:14,832
♪ It's... ♪

249
00:13:34,595 --> 00:13:38,920
Distinguished leaders,
guests, teachers, and students,

250
00:13:38,920 --> 00:13:39,959
good afternoon.

251
00:13:39,959 --> 00:13:41,319
Welcome! Welcome!

252
00:13:41,319 --> 00:13:44,679
Today is a special day.

253
00:13:44,679 --> 00:13:46,880
We gather here

254
00:13:46,880 --> 00:13:48,240
to welcome

255
00:13:48,240 --> 00:13:50,880
our foreign guests and

256
00:13:50,880 --> 00:13:54,679
enjoy pleasant conversations together.

257
00:13:54,679 --> 00:13:56,745
- Welcome.
- Hello.

258
00:13:56,745 --> 00:13:58,959
- Welcome. Welcome.
- Thank you.

259
00:13:58,959 --> 00:14:02,671
Welcome to No.1 Middle School in Anzi County.

260
00:14:02,671 --> 00:14:05,719
This is our school's chairman, Mr. Zhong.

261
00:14:05,719 --> 00:14:07,360
This is our dean,

262
00:14:07,360 --> 00:14:08,760
Ms. Yang.

263
00:14:08,760 --> 00:14:12,160
Today's journey will be led
by these two students.

264
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:13,520
This is Ye Ying Jian.

265
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:15,400
Hi. My name is Ye Ying Jian.

266
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:17,839
This is our student, Qing Ye.

267
00:14:17,839 --> 00:14:19,909
Hi, I'm Qing Ye. Nice to meet you.

268
00:14:19,909 --> 00:14:20,959
Nice to meet you too.

269
00:14:20,959 --> 00:14:22,800
So we shall start this journey.

270
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:24,479
- This way.
- Thank you.

271
00:14:24,479 --> 00:14:27,040
This way. Please follow us.

272
00:14:27,040 --> 00:14:28,088
Hi, guys.

273
00:14:28,088 --> 00:14:31,839
Welcome to No.1 Middle
School of Anzi County.

274
00:14:31,839 --> 00:14:33,760
We are located in Anzi County

275
00:14:33,760 --> 00:14:37,295
surrounded by beautiful seaside scenery.

276
00:14:37,295 --> 00:14:42,280
Yes. And also the campus
is well equipped with high-tech facilities

277
00:14:42,280 --> 00:14:44,400
including modern classrooms,

278
00:14:44,400 --> 00:14:46,280
advanced libraries

279
00:14:46,280 --> 00:14:49,095
and a big gymnasium.

280
00:14:50,240 --> 00:14:52,839
You should look at the walls. Both sides.

281
00:14:52,839 --> 00:14:56,160
There are Chinese famous models.

282
00:14:56,160 --> 00:14:58,182
Yes, I know this one.

283
00:14:58,182 --> 00:14:59,257
Loo-Keng Hua.

284
00:14:59,257 --> 00:15:00,799
Yes. You know that.

285
00:15:00,799 --> 00:15:02,199
It's our classroom.

286
00:15:02,199 --> 00:15:04,280
Okay.

287
00:15:04,280 --> 00:15:06,957
This is my class.

288
00:15:08,799 --> 00:15:10,457
Everyone, stand up.

289
00:15:10,457 --> 00:15:12,907
Applause, please!

290
00:15:15,760 --> 00:15:17,435
Come in.

291
00:15:21,760 --> 00:15:23,319
The fish tank thermostat is broken.

292
00:15:23,319 --> 00:15:25,920
Customer support said
repairs won't happen for two weeks.

293
00:15:25,920 --> 00:15:29,517
All these fish will definitely die by then.

294
00:15:37,040 --> 00:15:38,559
The tube's broken.

295
00:15:38,559 --> 00:15:40,400
It's an easy repair.

296
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:42,799
The water's still cold.

297
00:15:42,799 --> 00:15:45,079
The temperature system must be broken.

298
00:15:45,079 --> 00:15:46,920
Is it much trouble to fix?

299
00:15:46,920 --> 00:15:48,280
No.

300
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:50,480
If the digital thermometer goes wrong,

301
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:54,000
the heater can't get real-time
temperature readings,

302
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:56,599
so the heating system just won't kick on.

303
00:15:56,599 --> 00:16:00,470
Glad I came to the right person.

304
00:16:02,040 --> 00:16:04,439
Is really well planted?

305
00:16:04,439 --> 00:16:05,982
Yeah. It's bringing us fresh air.

306
00:16:05,982 --> 00:16:08,199
Yeah. We can enjoy some fresh air.

307
00:16:08,199 --> 00:16:10,120
It's a really good place for students.

308
00:16:10,120 --> 00:16:11,719
Oh, what's this place for?

309
00:16:11,719 --> 00:16:13,857
Oh, this is our English Corner.

310
00:16:13,857 --> 00:16:14,951
Hey, guys.

311
00:16:14,951 --> 00:16:16,920
- Hello, everyone.
- Nice to meet you.

312
00:16:16,920 --> 00:16:18,400
Nice to meet you too.

313
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:22,779
We always study here
and we can exchange our ideas.

314
00:16:27,760 --> 00:16:29,426
What is this?

315
00:16:29,426 --> 00:16:31,640
This item is called a badge.

316
00:16:31,640 --> 00:16:33,040
It's referred to as

317
00:16:33,040 --> 00:16:34,400
"Baji" in Chinese.

318
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:37,520
It's extremely popular
among Chinese high schools.

319
00:16:37,520 --> 00:16:40,400
We use it for learning English with joy.

320
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:43,640
We also create some rap songs
tor learn grammar and vocabulary.

321
00:16:43,640 --> 00:16:45,199
- Really?
- Yeah. Want to see?

322
00:16:45,199 --> 00:16:46,479
Yeah, sure.

323
00:16:46,479 --> 00:16:49,067
Showtime, Hu!

324
00:16:51,345 --> 00:16:53,882
Hello, everyone. My name is Fan Tong.

325
00:16:53,882 --> 00:16:55,319
You can call me Hu.

326
00:16:55,319 --> 00:16:58,120
It means "Fat Tiger."
But I'm not fat as you can see.

327
00:16:58,120 --> 00:16:59,520
I'll show you

328
00:16:59,520 --> 00:17:03,157
how we learn English with joy in rap.

329
00:17:04,163 --> 00:17:06,007
One, two, three, go!

330
00:17:06,007 --> 00:17:07,999
Welcome to
a totally different English class!

331
00:17:07,999 --> 00:17:10,320
♪ Today we learn words with rap
Don't stress out ♪

332
00:17:10,320 --> 00:17:12,463
♪ Only a handful of words and a verb suffix ♪

333
00:17:12,463 --> 00:17:14,880
♪ It's "act", pronounced [ækt] ♪

334
00:17:14,880 --> 00:17:17,120
♪ Today I step up here to become an actor ♪

335
00:17:17,120 --> 00:17:19,400
♪ If I overdo the act, it's called overact ♪

336
00:17:19,400 --> 00:17:21,400
♪ Rote learning brings outcomes
that counteract ♪

337
00:17:21,400 --> 00:17:25,307
♪ We influence and improve together
Let's interact together ♪

338
00:17:26,759 --> 00:17:28,820
Thank you.

339
00:17:30,120 --> 00:17:34,239
I'm really amazed by the English proficiency
of the students here

340
00:17:34,239 --> 00:17:35,595
and by

341
00:17:35,595 --> 00:17:37,600
the educational concept.

342
00:17:37,600 --> 00:17:40,519
We can talk about collaboration later.

343
00:17:41,519 --> 00:17:43,132
Okay.

344
00:17:56,120 --> 00:17:57,120
Go! Go! Go!

345
00:17:57,120 --> 00:17:58,999
Go for it!

346
00:17:59,695 --> 00:18:00,719
Do you like it?

347
00:18:00,719 --> 00:18:02,880
I really like basketball.

348
00:18:02,880 --> 00:18:05,082
Do you want to try?

349
00:18:06,696 --> 00:18:08,332
Okay, have a try.

350
00:18:08,332 --> 00:18:09,959
Thank you.

351
00:18:09,959 --> 00:18:11,570
Let's go.

352
00:18:16,160 --> 00:18:18,400
Okay. It's lunchtime.

353
00:18:18,400 --> 00:18:20,519
So shall we go to the restaurant to eat?

354
00:18:20,519 --> 00:18:21,560
Yeah. Sure.

355
00:18:21,560 --> 00:18:23,057
Let's go.

356
00:18:23,057 --> 00:18:26,770
- This way.
- I really love Chinese food.

357
00:18:32,320 --> 00:18:33,920
Ye Ying Jian is pretty good.

358
00:18:33,920 --> 00:18:36,057
He's won so many awards.

359
00:18:52,199 --> 00:18:54,757
He's a match for you, Wu.

360
00:19:08,480 --> 00:19:12,152
[Aerospace Cup Award Certificate]

361
00:19:16,120 --> 00:19:18,295
Don't touch anything.

362
00:19:20,840 --> 00:19:21,920
Xing Wu.

363
00:19:21,920 --> 00:19:24,012
Come see if the light tube you need is here.

364
00:19:24,012 --> 00:19:25,743
Okay.

365
00:19:28,199 --> 00:19:30,407
Look at the camera.

366
00:19:30,407 --> 00:19:33,995
Qing Ye. Ye Ying Jian.
Stand in the middle, please.

367
00:19:33,995 --> 00:19:35,239
Come on, come on.

368
00:19:35,239 --> 00:19:37,882
- I really like you guys.
- Thank you.

369
00:19:37,882 --> 00:19:38,920
Thank you.

370
00:19:38,920 --> 00:19:40,239
Please.

371
00:19:40,239 --> 00:19:42,160
- Thank you so much.
- Okay, everyone look at the camera.

372
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:45,982
One, two, three!

373
00:19:53,160 --> 00:19:54,239
Done.

374
00:19:54,239 --> 00:19:55,600
Already?

375
00:19:55,600 --> 00:19:58,995
First time fixing a fish tank?
Way quicker than fixing an air conditioner.

376
00:19:58,995 --> 00:20:00,400
Let's pack up.

377
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:01,895
Xing Wu.

378
00:20:01,895 --> 00:20:03,120
You're really good.

379
00:20:03,120 --> 00:20:04,682
Contact me if anything comes up.

380
00:20:04,682 --> 00:20:06,570
Okay.

381
00:20:06,570 --> 00:20:08,160
Mr. Jiang.

382
00:20:08,160 --> 00:20:10,519
Yes, I understand what you mean.

383
00:20:10,519 --> 00:20:11,557
Actually,

384
00:20:11,557 --> 00:20:13,080
I'd love to work with you.

385
00:20:13,080 --> 00:20:16,039
I just don't have the right project
on hand now.

386
00:20:17,039 --> 00:20:18,857
The fish tank is fixed?

387
00:20:19,857 --> 00:20:21,759
Right, right. How about this?

388
00:20:21,759 --> 00:20:23,719
Let's talk another day.

389
00:20:23,719 --> 00:20:26,199
Alright, okay.

390
00:20:27,199 --> 00:20:28,995
You're Xing Wu?

391
00:20:28,995 --> 00:20:30,400
Hello, Mr. Ye.

392
00:20:30,400 --> 00:20:31,400
Hello.

393
00:20:31,400 --> 00:20:33,320
Shu Han said you're smart and

394
00:20:33,320 --> 00:20:34,800
just as skilled as the official technicians.

395
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:36,320
I didn't buy it before.

396
00:20:36,320 --> 00:20:37,345
There's a trick to it.

397
00:20:37,345 --> 00:20:39,151
It's not that hard.

398
00:20:40,080 --> 00:20:43,320
You've done a great job in Xinhai County.

399
00:20:43,320 --> 00:20:45,519
You look about the same age as my son.

400
00:20:45,519 --> 00:20:47,840
Why aren't you studying anymore?

401
00:20:48,840 --> 00:20:50,199
I want to make money.

402
00:20:50,199 --> 00:20:52,207
You want to make money?

403
00:20:52,207 --> 00:20:54,200
Why do you want to make money?

404
00:20:54,200 --> 00:20:56,480
Who doesn't want to make money?

405
00:20:57,080 --> 00:20:58,199
[Ma Ming]

406
00:20:58,199 --> 00:21:00,662
Excuse me, I have to take this call.

407
00:21:01,332 --> 00:21:03,007
Hello? Mr. Ma.

408
00:21:03,007 --> 00:21:04,279
Wu.

409
00:21:04,279 --> 00:21:06,695
Mr. Ye seems quite interested in you.

410
00:21:06,695 --> 00:21:09,759
Congratulations.
Looks like you've won over another boss.

411
00:21:09,759 --> 00:21:12,267
I'm only interested in making money.

412
00:21:19,840 --> 00:21:21,719
Mr. Ye has taken notice of you.

413
00:21:21,719 --> 00:21:24,360
He's setting up the Electronics Zone
in the new mall.

414
00:21:24,360 --> 00:21:27,600
He wants to know
if you'd like to come and help run things.

415
00:21:27,600 --> 00:21:30,759
Wu. I told you he was interested in you.

416
00:21:30,759 --> 00:21:34,439
He was really satisfied with the batch
of computers you refurbished in Xinhai.

417
00:21:34,439 --> 00:21:36,719
He was really impressed by you.

418
00:21:36,719 --> 00:21:38,920
We only met for under three minutes.

419
00:21:38,920 --> 00:21:40,400
That is enough.

420
00:21:40,400 --> 00:21:42,439
Mr. Ye has been in business for years.

421
00:21:42,439 --> 00:21:44,279
He's got a great eye for people.

422
00:21:44,279 --> 00:21:45,600
Let me ask you.

423
00:21:45,600 --> 00:21:48,239
If Mr. Ye really offers you this chance,

424
00:21:48,239 --> 00:21:50,102
what do you think?

425
00:21:51,039 --> 00:21:52,039
What's the pay like?

426
00:21:52,039 --> 00:21:53,120
Wu.

427
00:21:53,120 --> 00:21:55,239
You'd be in charge of the
entire Electronics Zone.

428
00:21:55,239 --> 00:21:57,870
This is a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity.

429
00:21:57,870 --> 00:21:58,907
Exactly.

430
00:21:58,907 --> 00:22:01,759
Everyone's after this great gig.

431
00:22:01,759 --> 00:22:04,719
Even Yang Gang is competing for it.

432
00:22:05,719 --> 00:22:07,479
I need to know exactly what's on the table

433
00:22:07,479 --> 00:22:09,745
before I make up my mind.

434
00:22:09,745 --> 00:22:11,999
The base salary is 9,000 yuan,
plus generous commissions.

435
00:22:11,999 --> 00:22:13,160
You'll also get social insurance
and housing fund.

436
00:22:13,160 --> 00:22:14,279
If you stay for three years

437
00:22:14,279 --> 00:22:16,080
and wish to keep working here,

438
00:22:16,080 --> 00:22:17,759
Mr. Ye will let you

439
00:22:17,759 --> 00:22:19,800
take over the shop at a low price.

440
00:22:19,800 --> 00:22:20,800
What's more,

441
00:22:20,800 --> 00:22:22,920
Mr. Ye is currently developing real estate.

442
00:22:22,920 --> 00:22:24,057
You might

443
00:22:24,057 --> 00:22:26,482
even get an apartment from him.

444
00:22:31,239 --> 00:22:32,345
I hope

445
00:22:32,345 --> 00:22:35,439
we can spend a fun and unforgettable
high school time together.

446
00:22:35,439 --> 00:22:37,400
Let's leave here and

447
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:40,132
step into a shining new future.

448
00:22:45,479 --> 00:22:47,240
You're still on the fence with this offer?

449
00:22:47,240 --> 00:22:50,189
When do we meet Mr. Ye face to face?

450
00:22:51,439 --> 00:22:52,840
As soon as possible.

451
00:22:52,840 --> 00:22:54,800
Okay.

452
00:22:54,800 --> 00:22:57,313
[Youth Connects with the World
Foreign Guests Visit Exhibition]

453
00:23:02,880 --> 00:23:04,080
Cao Fan.

454
00:23:04,080 --> 00:23:07,245
Why does Qing Ye
get to steal all the spotlight?

455
00:23:07,920 --> 00:23:10,439
Because she really is outstanding.

456
00:23:10,439 --> 00:23:11,719
You're still praising her?

457
00:23:11,719 --> 00:23:13,279
Have you lost your mind?

458
00:23:13,279 --> 00:23:14,479
Yeah, Cao Fan.

459
00:23:14,479 --> 00:23:17,125
You got played and you're still defending her?

460
00:23:17,999 --> 00:23:19,600
Qing Ye is from the big city.

461
00:23:19,600 --> 00:23:21,959
She has a good family background
and is close with the teachers.

462
00:23:21,959 --> 00:23:23,199
I'm just not as good as her.

463
00:23:23,199 --> 00:23:24,479
I accept that.

464
00:23:24,479 --> 00:23:26,279
That was supposed to be your chance.

465
00:23:26,279 --> 00:23:27,800
If she hadn't interfered,

466
00:23:27,800 --> 00:23:31,245
you'd have been in that photo
with Ye Ying Jian.

467
00:23:31,999 --> 00:23:33,880
How can girls like us

468
00:23:33,880 --> 00:23:35,279
ever compete with her?

469
00:23:35,279 --> 00:23:38,770
We try our hardest,
but we're only at her starting line.

470
00:23:38,770 --> 00:23:41,800
I just can't stand her stuck-up, smug attitude.

471
00:23:41,800 --> 00:23:44,857
She's a new transfer,
yet she's stealing all the attention.

472
00:23:44,857 --> 00:23:47,107
Why's she so full of herself?

473
00:23:47,107 --> 00:23:49,795
Well, she's got the privileges to act that way.

474
00:23:49,795 --> 00:23:50,999
You can tolerate it,

475
00:23:50,999 --> 00:23:53,107
but I can't.

476
00:24:00,832 --> 00:24:02,239
Qing Ye.

477
00:24:02,239 --> 00:24:03,320
I was looking for you.

478
00:24:03,320 --> 00:24:04,840
Mr. Zhu.

479
00:24:04,840 --> 00:24:05,999
Here, take this.

480
00:24:05,999 --> 00:24:07,120
What is this?

481
00:24:07,120 --> 00:24:09,039
Your scholarship.
I promised it to you last time.

482
00:24:09,039 --> 00:24:11,120
This is your reward
for bringing honor to the school.

483
00:24:11,120 --> 00:24:13,679
Thank you, Mr. Zhu.

484
00:24:14,679 --> 00:24:15,920
Qing Ye,

485
00:24:15,920 --> 00:24:19,959
we don't have the same
good resources as schools in big cities.

486
00:24:19,959 --> 00:24:21,279
Yet as long as you keep working hard,

487
00:24:21,279 --> 00:24:23,645
we will spare no effort to nurture you.

488
00:24:23,645 --> 00:24:24,695
I understand.

489
00:24:24,695 --> 00:24:28,007
- Alright. I'm off.
- Goodbye, Mr. Zhu.

490
00:24:40,160 --> 00:24:43,000
[School-level Honor Scholarship]

491
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:47,457
I got a scholarship.

492
00:24:48,457 --> 00:24:50,166
Congratulations.

493
00:24:51,479 --> 00:24:56,080
This eases your financial stress, right?

494
00:24:56,080 --> 00:24:57,840
Nice windfall.

495
00:24:57,840 --> 00:24:58,870
So,

496
00:24:58,870 --> 00:25:01,727
how about coming back to school?

497
00:25:04,132 --> 00:25:05,182
It's not a windfall.

498
00:25:05,182 --> 00:25:07,252
You deserve this payment.

499
00:25:09,439 --> 00:25:12,527
Hiring a simultaneous interpreter
would cost more than this.

500
00:25:35,519 --> 00:25:37,120
What's up?

501
00:25:37,120 --> 00:25:40,360
These are gifts for you.

502
00:25:40,360 --> 00:25:41,679
This tames

503
00:25:41,679 --> 00:25:44,870
all the stuck-up show-offs.

504
00:25:48,080 --> 00:25:50,155
Are these few enough?

505
00:25:50,840 --> 00:25:53,295
Take all of them.

506
00:25:55,999 --> 00:25:59,720
They're all yours.

507
00:26:17,560 --> 00:26:20,722
[Xuan Island Barbershop]

508
00:26:32,360 --> 00:26:34,320
Hey, school's out, right?

509
00:26:34,320 --> 00:26:37,479
Wu. Hu and I got detention from Zhu Feng
for unfinished homework.

510
00:26:37,479 --> 00:26:39,595
Where's Qing Ye?

511
00:26:39,595 --> 00:26:41,360
She didn't leave with us.

512
00:26:41,360 --> 00:26:44,382
She's not back yet?

513
00:26:54,039 --> 00:26:55,882
Where did you go?

514
00:26:56,479 --> 00:26:58,595
I can't make it to Mr. Ye's dinner tonight.

515
00:26:58,595 --> 00:27:01,028
I'll pay him a visit to apologize tomorrow.

516
00:27:20,280 --> 00:27:22,240
Qing Ye.

517
00:27:22,240 --> 00:27:23,920
Where did you go?

518
00:27:23,920 --> 00:27:26,282
You didn't answer any of my calls.

519
00:27:26,282 --> 00:27:28,855
I had it on silent.

520
00:27:45,000 --> 00:27:46,671
Who did this?

521
00:27:47,560 --> 00:27:49,487
Does it matter?

522
00:28:09,560 --> 00:28:11,425
Stop cutting.

523
00:28:26,880 --> 00:28:28,655
Lie down.

524
00:28:56,120 --> 00:28:58,032
Does it hurt?

525
00:28:59,439 --> 00:29:01,520
What do you think?

526
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:05,957
It doesn't matter if it hurts.

527
00:29:05,957 --> 00:29:09,223
I just never want to see these things
ever again in my life.

528
00:29:19,160 --> 00:29:21,047
Are you hurt anywhere else?

529
00:29:21,840 --> 00:29:23,295
No.

530
00:29:24,040 --> 00:29:25,927
You're not lying to me?

531
00:29:29,480 --> 00:29:31,350
I'm not lying.

532
00:29:34,800 --> 00:29:36,617
That's good.

533
00:29:38,720 --> 00:29:40,325
Xing Wu.

534
00:29:40,995 --> 00:29:43,366
Come back to school with me.

535
00:29:51,519 --> 00:29:53,857
If you come back with me,

536
00:29:54,600 --> 00:29:57,238
no one will dare to bully me.

537
00:30:01,120 --> 00:30:03,895
How did you reach that conclusion?

538
00:30:05,679 --> 00:30:08,814
You're quite famous around here.

539
00:30:08,814 --> 00:30:10,360
My deskmate Shi Min

540
00:30:10,360 --> 00:30:13,120
really looks up to you.

541
00:30:13,120 --> 00:30:16,039
If you had my back,

542
00:30:16,039 --> 00:30:18,570
those troublemakers in my class

543
00:30:18,570 --> 00:30:21,024
wouldn't bug me.

544
00:30:24,279 --> 00:30:26,778
Wouldn't you do it just to protect me?

545
00:31:19,759 --> 00:31:21,640
Dry your hair yourself.

546
00:31:21,640 --> 00:31:23,603
I'm off for a bit.

547
00:31:26,959 --> 00:31:28,951
Xing Wu.

548
00:31:37,600 --> 00:31:38,959
Let me tell you.

549
00:31:38,959 --> 00:31:40,840
Zhu Feng keeps me behind
for homework every day.

550
00:31:40,840 --> 00:31:43,193
Like I don't have a life at home!

551
00:31:45,239 --> 00:31:46,560
I don't think

552
00:31:46,560 --> 00:31:48,560
studying is the only way out.

553
00:31:48,560 --> 00:31:49,800
I want to follow Wu,

554
00:31:49,800 --> 00:31:51,640
get a job and support my family.

555
00:31:51,640 --> 00:31:54,039
Come on. Look at you.

556
00:31:54,039 --> 00:31:56,160
I'm... I'm capable too.

557
00:31:56,160 --> 00:31:58,107
- I...
- Is it good?

558
00:31:58,719 --> 00:31:59,840
Wu.

559
00:31:59,840 --> 00:32:01,120
Why are you here?

560
00:32:01,120 --> 00:32:03,400
Wu, has Qing Ye gone home?

561
00:32:04,695 --> 00:32:05,795
Yes.

562
00:32:05,795 --> 00:32:08,099
Have some? I'll order one for you.

563
00:32:10,439 --> 00:32:12,080
You two, be honest.

564
00:32:12,080 --> 00:32:14,570
Is Qing Ye getting along well at school?

565
00:32:14,570 --> 00:32:15,582
Yeah.

566
00:32:15,582 --> 00:32:16,646
She's doing great.

567
00:32:16,646 --> 00:32:19,208
She's currently the star of our school.

568
00:32:21,272 --> 00:32:23,360
Has she rubbed anyone

569
00:32:23,360 --> 00:32:25,810
the wrong way at school?

570
00:32:27,279 --> 00:32:28,820
I don't think so.

571
00:32:28,820 --> 00:32:29,999
Not really.

572
00:32:29,999 --> 00:32:31,679
She's just been in the limelight lately.

573
00:32:31,679 --> 00:32:34,526
Foreign guests came to our school recently,
and she greeted them at the gate.

574
00:32:34,526 --> 00:32:37,045
Her English is... So fluent.

575
00:32:37,045 --> 00:32:39,120
All we could do
was stand aside with little flags,

576
00:32:39,120 --> 00:32:40,239
shouting, "Welcome! Welcome!".

577
00:32:40,239 --> 00:32:42,840
She's got quite a few admirers now,
both guys and girls.

578
00:32:42,840 --> 00:32:45,270
Did something happen?

579
00:32:46,600 --> 00:32:47,820
No.

580
00:32:47,820 --> 00:32:49,462
Just asking.

581
00:32:50,120 --> 00:32:51,360
I'm telling you, Wu,

582
00:32:51,360 --> 00:32:52,759
don't worry.

583
00:32:52,759 --> 00:32:56,320
She's not so easy to pick on.
She's not that fragile.

584
00:32:56,320 --> 00:32:58,107
But Wu,

585
00:32:58,107 --> 00:33:00,640
big names draw fire.

586
00:33:00,640 --> 00:33:02,840
A few folks

587
00:33:02,840 --> 00:33:05,144
are jealous of her.

588
00:33:06,039 --> 00:33:07,070
Who?

589
00:33:07,070 --> 00:33:09,719
She gets good grades, and she's pretty.

590
00:33:09,719 --> 00:33:12,148
I'd be jealous too if I were a girl.

591
00:33:15,920 --> 00:33:17,931
Who?

592
00:33:30,279 --> 00:33:32,770
You look just like your mom.

593
00:33:33,519 --> 00:33:36,759
A lot of people say my facial features
are more like my dad's.

594
00:33:37,920 --> 00:33:39,840
That's nonsense.

595
00:33:39,840 --> 00:33:42,279
Your mom and I were friends for ten years.

596
00:33:42,279 --> 00:33:45,261
You look exactly like her when she was young.

597
00:33:46,519 --> 00:33:49,306
Why did you leave her?

598
00:33:51,880 --> 00:33:55,629
I had Wu before I got married.

599
00:34:00,470 --> 00:34:04,395
I was adopted by your grandparents.

600
00:34:04,395 --> 00:34:08,479
I relied on them for food and shelter.
Ashamed of my mistakes,

601
00:34:08,479 --> 00:34:11,357
I simply ran away.

602
00:34:13,400 --> 00:34:15,554
Do you miss her?

603
00:34:16,320 --> 00:34:17,559
Yes.

604
00:34:17,559 --> 00:34:19,159
Of course I do.

605
00:34:19,159 --> 00:34:22,439
But I've never gone back to see her.

606
00:34:22,439 --> 00:34:25,945
A single misstep can lead

607
00:34:25,945 --> 00:34:28,206
to total ruin.

608
00:34:34,639 --> 00:34:36,840
Look at me.

609
00:34:36,840 --> 00:34:38,720
My husband left,

610
00:34:38,720 --> 00:34:40,407
leaving behind piles of debt.

611
00:34:40,407 --> 00:34:43,360
My mother-in-law is paralyzed,
and my son had to drop out of school.

612
00:34:43,360 --> 00:34:46,119
But life still goes on.

613
00:34:46,119 --> 00:34:49,180
Each day alive is a gain.

614
00:34:50,932 --> 00:34:52,645
Auntie,

615
00:34:52,645 --> 00:34:54,159
you're really positive.

616
00:34:54,159 --> 00:34:55,200
Of course.

617
00:34:55,200 --> 00:34:57,840
I get by purely because of my mindset.

618
00:34:57,840 --> 00:35:00,760
How do you young people put it again?

619
00:35:00,760 --> 00:35:04,159
I'm a "happy puppy."

620
00:35:04,159 --> 00:35:06,959
Anyway, life can always be made to work.

621
00:35:06,959 --> 00:35:08,519
At the end of the day,

622
00:35:08,519 --> 00:35:10,970
we live just to be happy.

623
00:35:13,559 --> 00:35:15,119
Auntie,

624
00:35:15,119 --> 00:35:17,570
do you ever want

625
00:35:17,570 --> 00:35:21,007
Xing Wu to stop muddling along?

626
00:35:24,439 --> 00:35:25,959
Schopenhauer said,

627
00:35:25,959 --> 00:35:29,599
fate shuffles and deals the cards,

628
00:35:29,599 --> 00:35:31,760
while we get to play them.

629
00:35:31,760 --> 00:35:33,039
Life can be more

630
00:35:33,039 --> 00:35:35,800
than just muddling through.

631
00:35:35,800 --> 00:35:38,680
We can also choose
to play our cards strategically.

632
00:35:38,680 --> 00:35:41,999
Instead of muddling along
and letting life slip away,

633
00:35:41,999 --> 00:35:44,159
we ought to go all out

634
00:35:44,159 --> 00:35:47,131
and break free from fate's cycle.

635
00:35:48,479 --> 00:35:49,795
Ye,

636
00:35:50,470 --> 00:35:52,554
Schopenhauer really put it well.

637
00:35:53,270 --> 00:35:57,545
Shuffling, dealing, and playing cards...

638
00:36:01,200 --> 00:36:03,540
He must be good at mahjong, right?

639
00:36:05,119 --> 00:36:06,824
He must be.

640
00:36:07,880 --> 00:36:10,121
I definitely want to learn from him.

641
00:36:35,880 --> 00:36:37,795
Xing Wu.

642
00:37:15,480 --> 00:37:20,235
[Math Paper Score 136]

643
00:37:34,159 --> 00:37:36,772
Are you here to help tidy my room?

644
00:37:38,519 --> 00:37:41,079
You're overthinking it.

645
00:37:41,079 --> 00:37:42,557
I...

646
00:37:43,519 --> 00:37:45,240
I just came in to take a look.

647
00:37:45,240 --> 00:37:48,320
Your handwriting is quite nice.

648
00:37:48,320 --> 00:37:50,680
I accidentally noticed

649
00:37:50,680 --> 00:37:53,345
that your math grades are pretty good.

650
00:37:53,345 --> 00:37:55,145
That's all.

651
00:37:56,680 --> 00:37:58,282
Just winged it.

652
00:37:58,959 --> 00:38:00,732
"Humblebrag."

653
00:38:04,439 --> 00:38:07,308
Since you're here,
you need to learn to protect yourself.

654
00:38:09,439 --> 00:38:11,245
I'll teach you a move.

655
00:38:12,079 --> 00:38:13,680
Teach me your best stuff.

656
00:38:13,680 --> 00:38:15,820
I won't learn the simple ones.

657
00:38:16,519 --> 00:38:17,820
Fine.

658
00:38:18,479 --> 00:38:19,920
Come on.

659
00:38:19,920 --> 00:38:21,647
Grab me.

660
00:38:23,079 --> 00:38:24,400
How should I grab you?

661
00:38:24,400 --> 00:38:25,599
Any way you want.

662
00:38:25,599 --> 00:38:27,970
Like you're trying to pin me down.

663
00:38:56,999 --> 00:38:59,510
You hurt me!

664
00:39:00,720 --> 00:39:02,639
Are you okay?

665
00:39:02,639 --> 00:39:05,035
Is this what you wanted to teach me?

666
00:39:05,645 --> 00:39:07,670
What I wanted to teach you is,

667
00:39:07,670 --> 00:39:09,800
reacting with nothing
but retaliation when threatened

668
00:39:09,800 --> 00:39:12,224
is never a clever move.

669
00:39:40,039 --> 00:39:43,255
This is... This was my birthday present.

670
00:39:43,999 --> 00:39:46,134
It's quite unique.

671
00:39:47,360 --> 00:39:48,680
So...

672
00:39:48,680 --> 00:39:50,200
What I'm trying to say is,

673
00:39:50,200 --> 00:39:52,999
there's no foolproof self-defense skill
in real life.

674
00:39:52,999 --> 00:39:54,999
Skills mean nothing against

675
00:39:54,999 --> 00:39:56,519
overwhelming strength.

676
00:39:56,519 --> 00:39:58,245
Just like what I did just now.

677
00:39:58,245 --> 00:40:00,420
So what should I do?

678
00:40:00,995 --> 00:40:02,479
Run.

679
00:40:02,479 --> 00:40:04,280
Of all the stratagems, retreat is the best.

680
00:40:04,280 --> 00:40:06,680
Run as far as you can.

681
00:40:08,119 --> 00:40:09,920
Lesson over.

682
00:40:09,920 --> 00:40:12,070
You can go now.

683
00:40:23,400 --> 00:40:25,320
What if I can't outrun them?

684
00:40:25,320 --> 00:40:29,542
What if they catch up and keep picking on me?

685
00:40:31,320 --> 00:40:33,225
This guy...

686
00:40:51,200 --> 00:40:53,240
What if I can't outrun them?

687
00:40:53,240 --> 00:40:55,887
What if they catch up
and keep picking on me?

688
00:41:05,120 --> 00:41:06,880
Stop cutting.

689
00:41:12,200 --> 00:41:13,732
Xing Wu,

690
00:41:13,732 --> 00:41:16,332
come back to school with me.

691
00:41:33,760 --> 00:41:36,532
Tofu for sale!

692
00:41:36,532 --> 00:41:40,320
Freshly made tofu!

693
00:41:44,479 --> 00:41:48,061
Freshly made tofu!

694
00:43:16,800 --> 00:43:18,640
Ling Ling.

695
00:43:30,800 --> 00:43:32,647
Looking for me?

696
00:43:34,840 --> 00:43:36,207
No.

697
00:43:36,999 --> 00:43:38,200
You followed me all the way here

698
00:43:38,200 --> 00:43:40,172
to keep me safe?
